<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-243-029 </DOCNO><DOCID>09 728 865</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Magazine  Jan 15 1991 v10 n1 p208(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Microsoft Project for Windows. (Microsoft Corp.'s projectmanagement software)(Cover story: best of 1990) (Software Review)(evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Willmott, Don.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Microsoft Corp's Project for Windows, $695, is a projectmanagement program that takes full advantage of Windows 3.0'sgraphical interface and offers a very user-friendly environmentwith excellent graphics.andP;  Project for Windows provides schedulingand tracking features.andP;  Users can create views of a project andany two views can be displayed together for easy comparison.andP;  Theprogram gives users control over formats of screen displays andprinted reports.andP;  Users can manipulate font type and size as wellas styles and colors of connecting lines and task bars.andP;  Projectfor Windows lacks several features, including cost diagrams,priorities for projects, the ability to work with inflation costsand a time-scaled network diagram.andP;  System requirements include1Mbyte of RAM, DOS 3.0 or later and Windows 3.0.andP;  A mouse isrecommended.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (Products).andO;Ticker:    MSFT.andO;Product:   Project for Windows (Project management software) (evaluation).andO;Topic:     Project ManagementSoftware packagesEvaluation.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>If any one application is utterly transformed by a graphical interface, it'sproject management.andP;  Sure, over the years we've seen project managementpackages that have operated either under Windows or with a proprietarygraphical interface, but the arrival of Windows 3.0 last May and MicrosoftProject for Windows soon after really showed us what project management canand should be.andM;This $695 Editor's Choice invites new project management users to experimentwith the concept in a friendly, up-front environment mercifully devoid of anunending series of intimidating task forms to fill out.andM;The package has a complete set of scheduling and tracking features, all ofwhich are presented with excellent graphics in clear, functional datascreens.andP;  Creating new views of a project is usually a matter of clicking ona couple of icons, and any two views can be displayed together so that youcan, for example, combine a Gantt chart with a PERT chart or a histogram witha task form.andP;  You can also filter and customize these hybrid views and savethem for later use.andM;Project for Windows gives you unprecedented control over the formats of boththe on-screen displays and the printed reports, from font type and size tothe colors and styles of task bars and connecting lines.andP;  If you don't have avery good plotter before you buy this package, you'll soon see why you needone.andM;The Windows interface endows Project for Windows with the tools to manipulatethe task bars on the Gantt chart and the boxes on the PERT chart directly.andO;Though hardcore project managers may complain that such features are pureflash and that no one really plans a project that way, direct manipulation isa great way to play &quot;what-if&quot; and to brainstorm in a group.andP;  Pop-up boxes onthe Gantt chart present date information or task coordinates as you work withtask bars and scroll through the project.andM;Currently missing from Project for Windows are priorities for projects, costdiagrams, a time-scaled network diagram, and the ability to enter inflationcosts.andP;  Microsoft had better keep on its toes because the arrival of somepromising though as yet unreleased products may further shake up this market.andO;We're happy to hand out these laurels, but don't rest on them too long,Microsoft.andM;FACT FILEandM;Microsoft Project for Windows; Microsoft Corp., One Microsoft Way, Redmond,WA 98052;  800) 426-9400,(206) 882-8080.andM;List Price:  695.andP;  Requires: 1MB RAM, DOS 3.0 or later, Windows 3.0.andP;  Mouserecommended.andP;  Reviewed: September 11, 1990, page 352.andO;</TEXT></DOC>